# Mad-Thinkers
# 🛒 SuperShop Management System

A Java desktop application with a Swing GUI that simulates day-to-day retail shop operations. Built as a project for **CSE 202: Object Oriented Programming I Lab**, University of Asia Pacific.

The system provides role-based login portals for **Admins** and **Employees**, complete inventory and billing workflows, and persistent CSV-based data storage — all designed around core Java OOP principles.

---

## ✨ Features

### Admin Dashboard
- Full CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) on employee records
- Real-time daily sales report
- Low-stock alerts with an integrated restock workflow

### Employee Dashboard
- Add, search, update, and delete inventory items (Standard & Discount types)
- Shopping-cart style billing system
- Itemised, formatted customer invoice generation

### Data Persistence
- All employee records, inventory, and invoice history are stored in CSV files
- Auto-creates default Admin account and data directory on first run
- Resumes bill numbering correctly across sessions

### Robust Error Handling
- Graceful handling of `NumberFormatException`, `IOException`, `FileNotFoundException`, and `NullPointerException`
- Input validation and retry prompts to prevent crashes

---

## 🏗️ OOP Concepts Applied

| Concept | Implementation |
|---|---|
| **Abstraction** | Abstract `User` and `Item` classes define shared contracts |
| **Inheritance** | `Admin`/`Employee` extend `User`; `StandardItem`/`DiscountItem` extend `Item` |
| **Encapsulation** | Private/protected fields exposed only via getters and setters |
| **Polymorphism** | `calculatePrice()` overridden per item type; resolved at runtime |

The application also follows an **MVC-inspired architecture**, where View classes (`LoginFrame`, `AdminDashboard`, `EmployeeDashboard`) contain no business logic — all data processing is delegated to Controller classes (`AuthController`, `EmployeeController`, `ItemController`, `BillController`).

